<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910515-0114</DOCNO><DOCID>910515-0114.</DOCID><HL>   Zurn Industries Plant Contract</HL><DATE>05/15/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C13</SO><CO>   ZRN</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>HEAVY CONSTRUCTION; INDUSTRIAL AND COMMERCIAL (CON)ELECTRIC UTILITIES (ELC)</IN><RE>PENNSYLVANIA (PA)MAINE (ME)</RE><LP>   ERIE, Pa. -- Zurn Industries Inc. said it received a $40million contract for a wastewood power generation plant forAlternative Energy Inc. of Bangor, Maine.   The company said the contract calls for Zurn's Zurn/Nepcounit to design and build a 34-megawatt wood-burning powerplant at Livermore Falls, Maine. Electricity produced at thenew facility will be sold to Central Maine Power.Construction should be completed by the fall of 1992.</LP><TEXT>   Zurn is a maker of energy and environmental equipment.</TEXT></DOC>